000:metadata/org.awaitility/awaitility/index.json:25:    \"description\" : \"Awaitility is a Java DSL for waiting on asynchronous operations in tests without manual sleeps or polling loops. It lets assertions poll until conditions are satisfied or time out, making concurrent and eventually consistent behavior easier to verify.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1005:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-wordspec_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\": \"ScalaTest WordSpec provides the WordSpec style for writing behavior-driven ScalaTest suites using nested words and sentences to describe a system under test. It includes synchronous, asynchronous, and fixture-based suite classes that integrate with ScalaTest assertions, matchers, tagging, and test lifecycle features.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1010:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-refspec_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\": \"ScalaTest RefSpec provides the RefSpec testing style for ScalaTest on the JVM, where tests are represented by methods and discovered via reflection. It integrates with ScalaTest's core assertions, tagging, fixtures, and reporting so Scala projects can define and run method-oriented test suites.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1015:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-mustmatchers_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ScalaTest Must Matchers provides the must-style matcher syntax for ScalaTest assertions on the JVM. It supplies the org.scalatest.matchers.must.Matchers API, allowing tests to express expectations such as values must equal, include, contain, start with, or satisfy custom matchers.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1020:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-shouldmatchers_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\": \"ScalaTest Should Matchers provides the should matcher syntax for expressing assertions in ScalaTest suites. It lets tests compare values, inspect collections and properties, and build readable expectations using ScalaTest's matcher DSL.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1025:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-matchers-core_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\": \"ScalaTest Matchers Core provides the shared matcher result types, matcher abstractions, and DSL words used by ScalaTest's should and must matcher APIs. It lets Scala tests express type-safe assertions about equality, containment, ordering, patterns, properties, and custom matchers on the JVM.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1030:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-featurespec_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\": \"ScalaTest FeatureSpec provides the FeatureSpec and AsyncFeatureSpec testing style for organizing ScalaTest suites around named features and scenarios. It supplies synchronous, asynchronous, and fixture-based specs for behavior-driven Scala tests while integrating with ScalaTest's assertions, matchers, reporting, and runner infrastructure.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1035:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-compatible/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"scalatest-compatible provides the org.scalatest.compatible.Assertion marker interface used by ScalaTest-compatible assertion types. It lets third-party libraries define assertion results that can appear as the final expression in ScalaTest test bodies while avoiding Scala binary compatibility concerns.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1040:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-funsuite_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ScalaTest FunSuite provides the FunSuite testing style for ScalaTest on the JVM, where tests are registered as named functions rather than discovered as methods. It integrates with ScalaTest's assertions, fixtures, tagging, asynchronous suites, and reporting so Scala projects can write function-oriented unit tests.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1045:metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-funspec_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ScalaTest FunSpec provides the FunSpec style for writing behavior-driven ScalaTest suites with nested describe and it clauses. It includes synchronous, asynchronous, fixture-based, and path-based suite classes that integrate with ScalaTest assertions, tagging, and test lifecycle features.\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1324:org/glassfish/grizzly/http/ContentEncodingException.class\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1365:curl: (22) The requested URL returned error: 404\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1393:rl: (22) The requested URL returned error: 404\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1772:BUILD SUCCESSFUL in 3m 51s\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-09T01-45-41-391132Z.log:15:> Task :generateMetadata FAILED\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.grizzly:grizzly-http:2.1.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-09T01-45-41-391132Z.log:23:FAILURE: Build fa